<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F77FEF948F75411FD13FC15" pageId="313" pageNumber="314" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="007606418F77FEF948F75411FD13FC15" blockId="313.[151,1437,793,1178]" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F77FEF948F75411FEE4FCA6" bold="true" box="[199,321,829,854]" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F77FEF9497A5411FE3BFCA5" box="[330,414,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F77FEF949805411FDE7FCA5" box="[432,578,829,853]" captionStart="PLATE 88" captionStartId="306.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[183,1402,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-95@306.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="306" captionText="PLATE 88. A, C, D. Chelae, holotypes. B, E. Fore wings, holotypes. F, G. Male genitalia, holotypes. A. Dryinus viet (from Olmi 1984). B–D. Hybristodryinus resinicolus (from Engel 2005). E, F. D. maculipennis (from He &amp; Xu 2002). G. D. olmii (from Xu &amp; He 1994b). Scale bar 0.24 mm for A, 0.84 mm for B, 0.18 mm for C and G, 0.16 mm for D, 1.49 mm for E, 0.32 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278688/files/figure.png" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">Plate 88B–D</figureCitation>
); fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F77FEF94ACE5411FCCBFCA5" box="[766,878,829,853]" captionStart="PLATE 88" captionStartId="306.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[183,1402,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-95@306.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="306" captionText="PLATE 88. A, C, D. Chelae, holotypes. B, E. Fore wings, holotypes. F, G. Male genitalia, holotypes. A. Dryinus viet (from Olmi 1984). B–D. Hybristodryinus resinicolus (from Engel 2005). E, F. D. maculipennis (from He &amp; Xu 2002). G. D. olmii (from Xu &amp; He 1994b). Scale bar 0.24 mm for A, 0.84 mm for B, 0.18 mm for C and G, 0.16 mm for D, 1.49 mm for E, 0.32 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278688/files/figure.png" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">Plate 88B</figureCitation>
); occipital carina complete; mandible and palpal formula not visible; antenna without tufts of long hairs; antennal rhinaria not visible; fore wing with three cells enclosed by pigmented veins (costal, median and submedian) (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F77FEF94B4654A9FC4DFC6D" box="[886,1000,901,925]" captionStart="PLATE 88" captionStartId="306.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[183,1402,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-95@306.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="306" captionText="PLATE 88. A, C, D. Chelae, holotypes. B, E. Fore wings, holotypes. F, G. Male genitalia, holotypes. A. Dryinus viet (from Olmi 1984). B–D. Hybristodryinus resinicolus (from Engel 2005). E, F. D. maculipennis (from He &amp; Xu 2002). G. D. olmii (from Xu &amp; He 1994b). Scale bar 0.24 mm for A, 0.84 mm for B, 0.18 mm for C and G, 0.16 mm for D, 1.49 mm for E, 0.32 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278688/files/figure.png" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">Plate 88B</figureCitation>
); chela with rudimentary claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F77FEF94D5454A9FF4DFC31" captionStart="PLATE 88" captionStartId="306.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[183,1402,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-95@306.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="306" captionText="PLATE 88. A, C, D. Chelae, holotypes. B, E. Fore wings, holotypes. F, G. Male genitalia, holotypes. A. Dryinus viet (from Olmi 1984). B–D. Hybristodryinus resinicolus (from Engel 2005). E, F. D. maculipennis (from He &amp; Xu 2002). G. D. olmii (from Xu &amp; He 1994b). Scale bar 0.24 mm for A, 0.84 mm for B, 0.18 mm for C and G, 0.16 mm for D, 1.49 mm for E, 0.32 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278688/files/figure.png" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">Plate 88C–D</figureCitation>
); segment 5 of protarsus less than twice as broad as enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F77FEF94BCB5485FB28FC31" box="[1019,1165,937,961]" captionStart="PLATE 88" captionStartId="306.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[183,1402,224,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-95@306.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="306" captionText="PLATE 88. A, C, D. Chelae, holotypes. B, E. Fore wings, holotypes. F, G. Male genitalia, holotypes. A. Dryinus viet (from Olmi 1984). B–D. Hybristodryinus resinicolus (from Engel 2005). E, F. D. maculipennis (from He &amp; Xu 2002). G. D. olmii (from Xu &amp; He 1994b). Scale bar 0.24 mm for A, 0.84 mm for B, 0.18 mm for C and G, 0.16 mm for D, 1.49 mm for E, 0.32 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278688/files/figure.png" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">Plate 88C–D</figureCitation>
); enlarged claw shorter than protibia; tibial spurs 1/1/1. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F77FEF949CE54E1FD92FC15" box="[510,567,973,997]" italics="true" pageId="313" pageNumber="314">Male</emphasis>
; unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
